casebody.data:
Helena L. G. Asinari, Respondent v. Catharine Requa, impleaded with others, Appellant. Decided July 5, 1892. Appeal by defendant Requa from order her answer as frivolous and directing judgment in favor of plaintiff thereon. P. Van Alstine, for appellant. Gillender & Stoiber, for respondent.

Before Freedman, P. J., Dugro and Gildersleeve, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Order affirmed, with $10. costs and disbursements.
